last_episode_to_air.name: Defeat Or Three Peat
last_episode_to_air.overview: In the final event, the championship is within reach for both Ryan and Kye.

name: Street Outlaws: No Prep Kings
overview: Each week, Outlaws veteran "Chuck" will serve as race master in a new city and on a new "no prep" track, where 32 of the biggest names in no prep racing - including STREET OUTLAWS favorites, as well as newcomers - will duke it out to become the ultimate "no prep winner" and receive a $40,000 first place purse

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: America’s fastest track racers are back, and the stakes are higher than ever with new cars, new drivers, 15 events, and nearly $900,000 up for grabs.

episodes.name: Making It In Memphis
episodes.overview: Thirty-two of the best racers from around the country meet in Memphis to compete for $50,000 and the chance to earn points in the first No Prep Kings points series. But, rainy weather and a tricky track threaten to derail the racer's plans.

episodes.name: Memphis Money
episodes.overview: Sixteen racers remain in the first ever No Prep Kings Invitational, and as the racers move into round two, it's time to turn it up to try to win. With a little more data on the track, racers can push their cars further for a chance at the $50,000.

episodes.name: Ready, Set, Re-Do
episodes.overview: Thirty-two of the fastest racers around meet at Beech Bend Park in Bowling Green, Kentucky for the 2nd No Prep Kings invitational race. There's $40,000 & more points up for grabs, but trouble forces some of the racers to re-run their 1st round race

episodes.name: Bluegrass and Cash
episodes.overview: Sixteen racers move into round two of the No Prep Kings invitational race in Bowling Green, Kentucky. The track is slicker and more challenging, so the fastest racers from around the country do what they can to take home the $40,000 prize.

episodes.name: Texas Takedown
episodes.overview: Thirty-two of the fastest racers descend on Edinburgh, Texas for the next race and for a chance to win $40,000 plus more points. However, it's been raining in Texas and the track is probably the trickiest the racers will see all season.

episodes.name: When The Dust Settles
episodes.overview: The Street Outlaws are in Tucson, Arizona for the next No Prep Kings invitational race, and the dusty desert brings its own challenges. Birdman is out for blood, while Kye Kelley hopes to prove that he is really a contender in this series.

episodes.name: San Antonio Jumpstart
episodes.overview: Thirty-two racers head to San Antonio, Texas, for the fifth No Prep Kings invitational race where damp track conditions make it a little trickier, and a new design for the starting tree causes Kye Kelley to see red.

episodes.name: Lone Star Raincheck
episodes.overview: The fifth No Prep Kings invitational race continues in San Antonio, Texas, with 16 racers kicking off round two as they face off for a $40,000 prize. Weather causes a change of venue for rest of the race, and heavy hitters strive to become number one.

episodes.name: Carolina Callouts
episodes.overview: Ryan Martin, Chuck, and Birdman fight for the lead in points. This week, the racers are in Orangeburg, South Carolina, and with so much on the line, they use callouts and strategy to try to get ahead.

episodes.name: South Carolina Two Step
episodes.overview: The racers move into round two of the sixth No Prep race in South Carolina and as the track gets better, the racers turn it up to try to win. As eliminations continue, racers will have to fight to survive the fastest semi-finals and finals we've seen.

episodes.name: Tar Heelin and Dealin
episodes.overview: Racers arrive Dunn, NC, for the seventh race in the no prep kings series; after weeks and weeks of racing, many of the racers are struggling to keep their cars running, and, in a points series, consistency can be just as important as speed.

episodes.name: $40,000 and Dunn
episodes.overview: As the racers move into the later rounds of the second to last points race, all eyes are on Chuck, Birdman and Ryan Martin; a win in North Carolina could put Ryan one step closer to winning as long as he doesn't slip up.

episodes.name: OK, Let's Do This
episodes.overview: It's the final race of the No Prep Kings series, and that means that all eyes are on Birdman and Ryan Martin. If either of them can win the race in Tulsa, they'll walk away with the $40,000 prize plus $50,000 for the points championship.

episodes.name: Bristol: Race to $200K
episodes.overview: The second annual Bristol No Prep race begins with 32 of the fastest men and women competing for a giant, winner takes all, prize of $200,000. The competition heats up as racers push their cars round after round adjusting their tunes for the track.

episodes.name: Kick Off in Kansas
episodes.overview: The new season kicks off in Topeka, Kansas with the largest field of racers that No Prep Kings has ever seen. With a tricky track surface, and the fastest racers competing everyone has their work cut out for them to take home the $40,000.

episodes.name: Too Fast for Topeka
episodes.overview: Racers move into round two of the first No Prep Kings race of the season and with so much on the line, they push themselves and their cars to the limits. At the end of the night it's going to take a little luck and a lot of hard work to get the win.

episodes.name: Mo' Money Mo' Memphis
episodes.overview: The No Prep Kings Points Championship continues in Memphis Tennessee, where racers compete for $40,000 and points in the championship. Starting at the next event, the race is capped at 32 racers, and points determine who gets a spot in the next race.

episodes.name: Sweet Tunes in Memphis
episodes.overview: As racers move into round 2 in Memphis, the heat and humidity become more challenging as the track gets greasy and slicker. With $40,000 and valuable points on the line these drivers are willing to do anything to get from A to B to get the win.

episodes.name: Pennsylvania Thunder
episodes.overview: Racers arrive at Maple Grove Raceway for the 3rd event in the No Prep Kings series, but rain delays the start of the race. When it's time to start round 1, racers learn the hard way that the rainy weather has made this track especially challenging.

episodes.name: Pouring It On in PA
episodes.overview: Racers move into round 2 at Maple Grove Raceway, and leader Ryan Martin hopes to continue his winning streak. Meanwhile, heavy hitters like Mike Murillo, Chuck, Larry Larson, and Jeff Lutz try to take him out.

episodes.name: Crashing Chi-Town
episodes.overview: Racers arrive at Route 66 Raceway outside of Chicago for the fourth race in the No Prep Kings series. When cold weather and rainy conditions make the track extra sketchy, the racers have to be on their game if they want to make it to the finish line.

episodes.name: Runnin' Route 66
episodes.overview: Racers enter round two of the fourth event in the No Prep Kings series. After a challenging round one, the track is starting to come around. Racers have to turn their cars up without blowing tires off as they all chase points and the $40,000 prize.

episodes.name: Mile High Mayhem
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Morrison, Colorado for the next event in the No Prep Kings series, however, the high altitude means thin air and big problems for the racers who run turbos. It'll be a struggle just to get to the finish line.

episodes.name: Driving High
episodes.overview: It's time for the finals rounds in the race for points and $40,000 at Bandimere Speedway, but challenging conditions and a lengthy schedule are knocking out cars left and right. However, the top racers won't let the high altitude get them down.

episodes.name: Dust in the Wind
episodes.overview: Racers are in Tucson, AZ for the sixth race in the No Prep Kings points series, but the desert dust and heat mean a seriously sketchy surface. As the move into the final races of the season, the pressure has never been higher.

episodes.name: Desert Dollars
episodes.overview: It's day two of the sixth race in the No Prep Kings points series and when the sun comes out, the Tucson track gets even sketchier. And, with a rare chance to make up some serious ground, Mike Murillo is hoping to go rounds and earn some valuable points.

episodes.name: The Heart of It All
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Norwalk, Ohio for the seventh race in the No Prep Kings series and with only a few races left, the points race for the Championship is on. But, with a deceptively tricky track, the racers must find the right tune or risk going home.

episodes.name: Buckeye Battles
episodes.overview: Racers move into the second half of the seventh race in the No Prep Kings series, and with most of the top points leaders still in the race, the pressure is on for them to go all the way.

episodes.name: Go, Go, Go GALOT!
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Benson, North Carolina for the second to last No Prep Kings race of the season, but the track is trickier than normal. It's the last race before the double points finale, so for anyone with their eyes on the prize, it's now or never.

episodes.name: Coastin' in Carolina
episodes.overview: Racers are at GALOT Motorsports Park, and with most of the points leaders moving into the second half of the race, the pressure is on. It's the last race before the double points finale, so for anyone with their eyes on the prize, it's now or never.

episodes.name: Finally In Texas
episodes.overview: It's time for the final event of the No Prep Kings season, and the stakes have never been higher. This race is for double points, which means every round counts as Ryan Martin, Mike Murillo, and Larry Larson scramble to take home the $250,000.

episodes.name: Crowning the King
episodes.overview: After a dramatic round one, the race to the Points Championship is wide open. And, with everything on the line, the top racers are prepared to give everything they've got in order to earn the coveted title of No Prep King Points Champion.

episodes.name: Win One for the Team
episodes.overview: The top No Prep racers gather at Maryland International Raceway for the first event of the season. Alliances form amongst veterans and newcomers alike, and tensions rise as each new faction plots its course to the top of the standings.

episodes.name: NOLA Rising
episodes.overview: Team OKC arrives in New Hampshire fired up after an explosive start at Maryland International Raceway the week prior. With Texas keen to strike back, Kye realizes the only way NOLA can compete is if they also band together.

episodes.name: Let Them Eat Crow
episodes.overview: Big Chief is ready to make his No Prep debut as the racers roll into St. Louis for the third race of the season. NOLA is determined to deliver back-to-back upsets after the last race but the OKC and Texas aren't going down without a fight.

episodes.name: Lock It Up
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Idaho for the season's fourth race, everyone is focused on chasing down Lizzy. Ryan Martin tries a tricky new setup that could make or break his chances. As OKC, Texas, and NOLA band together, a new faction of misfits forms.

episodes.name: Game Time
episodes.overview: With the season half over and racers jockeying for points, the horseplay gets crazier than ever at Route 66 Raceway in Illinois. Lizzy & Team NOLA have been an unstoppable force so the competition is prepared to do anything to get ahead.

episodes.name: Route 66 Showdown
episodes.overview: With the season half over and racers jockeying for points, the horseplay gets crazier than ever at Route 66 Raceway in Illinois. Lizzy and Team NOLA have been an unstoppable force so the competition is prepared to do anything to get ahead.

episodes.name: Ruler of the Mountain
episodes.overview: Heading into the seventh race at Summit Motorsports Park in Ohio. Conditions remain unforgiving as the racers move into round two at Colorado's Bandimere Speedway. With so much on the line, even those who are struggling will stop at nothing to win and be crowned King or Queen of the Mountain.

episodes.name: Fireball Flameout
episodes.overview: With two races left in the season, drivers are hustling to rack up points. On the brink of another championship, Ryan feels the pressure. Team NOLA forms an unexpected alliance in an attempt to increase their chances of winning an NPK trophy.

episodes.name: Don't Choke
episodes.overview: Ryan rolls into the final event at the top of the leaderboard and with each round worth double points, the pressure is on to not let the elusive NPK trophy slip away for a third time. Kye, Lizzy and Scott do everything in their power to derail him.

episodes.name: Not So Peachy State
episodes.overview: In the 2nd points race, Ryan Martin and Murder Nova look to continue their strong starts. After a storm, racers struggle to adjust to an already dangerous track and a disagreement threatens to pull Team X apart.

episodes.name: Battle For The Crown
episodes.overview: A parts failure leaves Ryan Martin with a vulnerable target on his back.

episodes.name: Slow Burn
episodes.overview: At Maple Grove Raceway, Ryan Martin, Cody Baker and Eric Kvilhaug are in a three-way tie for first place. Murder Nova tries to figure out a way to help his team with a broken car and Chuck slow plays Justin Swanstrom.

episodes.name: Hot Mess
episodes.overview: Several weeks into the season, racers are struggling to keep their cars running at peak performance, working long days and long nights just to get race ready. Factor in extreme heat and a greasy surface, and someone’s bound to hit a wall.

episodes.name: Breaking Point
episodes.overview: Halfway through the season, competition heats up and strategy becomes more important than ever. Eric Bain pushes his car to its breaking point. Ryan Martin is back in first place, but another racer may find a way to close the gap quickly.

episodes.name: A Little Help From My Friends
episodes.overview: In the back half of the season, Ryan Martin, Eric K and Robin Roberts lead the field in points. With a couple of good passes and support from a fellow teammate, Kye Kelley hopes to push his way into the top three.

episodes.name: Two-For-One Special
episodes.overview: Coming off a Team Attack win, Ryan Martin goes for two victories in one weekend. Bobby Ducote gives Jerry Bird a push into the second round, and Murder Nova suffers a catastrophic failure.

episodes.name: Rule Breakers
episodes.overview: In Tucson, the 405 finds out that Texas may have broken the rules before the race even starts and the group must decide whether Texas should be disqualified. One dispute leads to another and two racers emerge as the front-runners amidst all the drama.

episodes.name: And the Fire Raged On
episodes.overview: After a slew of disagreements at the last event, some racers aren't ready to set aside their grudges. Ryan Martin remains the points leader with Kye Kelley right on his heels. To get to first, Kye will have to go through his girlfriend Lizzy first.

episodes.name: X Gonna Give It To Ya
episodes.overview: Racers are in the home stretch of the Points Competition. Ryan Martin is determined to claim the top spot in his home state, but Team X and Team NOLA are hot on his heels and ready to do whatever it takes to knock him down.

episodes.name: Texas Tussle
episodes.overview: Racers arrive in Texas for one of the final three races left in the points championship. Ryan Martin sits in first place, but with a small margin for error, one misstep could be his undoing.

episodes.name: Family Fists
episodes.overview: Racers arrive at No Problem Raceway for the second-to-last event of the season with Ryan Martin barely edging out his competition. Team OKC bands together to help him solidify his lead and tensions boil over when two NOLA teammates face off in the semis.

episodes.name: Don't Let Up
episodes.overview: The season comes down to one final race in Bradenton. Ryan Martin must choose between a first round callout from a teammate, and taking his chances drawing from the bucket. The rest of the field is ready to take him down, if he gives them the chance.

episodes.name: Let the No Prepping Begin
episodes.overview: Racers kick off a new season of No Prep Kings with a qualifier event and everyone is out to get two-time Points Champion Ryan Martin.

episodes.name: Watch Your Back
episodes.overview: Points competition officially begins and two-time champion Ryan Martin has a target on his back. And when his car gives him trouble, Team NOLA calls upon their heavy hitters to capitalize on his bad luck.

episodes.name: Break Up That Foursome
episodes.overview: The points race heats up at Maple Grove Raceway as Kye, Jerry Bird, Ryan Martin and Daddy Dave all try to break out of their four-way tie for first. But when they don't all make it out of the first round, it gives one of them a chance to steal the lead.

episodes.name: Luck of the Draw
episodes.overview: At New England Dragway, NOLA keeps getting in their own way when they can't keep from drawing each other and Ryan Martin makes a push to win his first race.

episodes.name: Little Bit of Contact
episodes.overview: Ryan Martin looks to take back the points lead, but others are doing what they can to knock him out and racers begrudgingly leave Team Texas.

episodes.name: New Racer on the Block
episodes.overview: Ryan is looking to extend his lead but Team NOLA is right on his heels. Plus, a new face goes rounds.

episodes.name: Weather or Not
episodes.overview: Racers struggle with unusual weather in Minnesota. Justin Swanstrom breaks away from Team X.

episodes.name: Hot Mess
episodes.overview: With Ryan in sole possession of the lead, NOLA tries to make some big moves to catch up.

episodes.name: What a Shocker!
episodes.overview: In Idaho, Kye Kelley reveals his new secret weapon and Team California makes a strong showing.

episodes.name: Upset in the Desert
episodes.overview: In Tucson, where the desert surface is tricky, there are plenty of upsets.

episodes.name: The Mile High Club
episodes.overview: The 32-car invitational is filled with upsets as many of the top racers struggle with the high elevation and thin air at Bandimere Speedway in Colorado.

episodes.name: Chasing Ryan
episodes.overview: Kye is chasing Ryan for the the points lead, but ends up dealing with car troubles.

episodes.name: Go for Broke
episodes.overview: Ryan changes motors right before the North Carolina Invitational

episodes.name: Vow to Destroy
episodes.overview: Kye's ambition to win may cost him his relationship with Lizzy.

episodes.name: Defeat Or Three Peat
episodes.overview: In the final event, the championship is within reach for both Ryan and Kye.

5.name: Season 5
5.overview: America’s fastest track racers are back, and the stakes are higher than ever with new cars, new drivers, 15 events, and nearly $900,000 up for grabs.
